---
title: Jammy Fig and Brie Grilled Cheese with Arugula Mushroom Salad
description: A classic grilled cheese hits the spot for breakfast or lunch. But if you’re going to do it for dinner, you gotta spiff it up. Our version is just fancy enough with brie and sweet fig jam, though all that melty cheese will still take you to a comfy, cozy place. We’re adding on an arugula mushroom salad not just because it’s delish, but also to help keep things classy.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/fig-and-brie-grilled-cheese-31750705.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/fig-and-brie-grilled-cheese-ebf1dcfd.pdf
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 517 kcal
  fat: 30 g
  saturated fat: 15 g
  carbohydrates: 48 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 21 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 753 mg
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/jammy-fig-and-brie-grilled-cheese-58580b4e4348d23f907b9d12
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
time required: 25 minutes
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat #oven{} to 400 degrees. Strip @rosemary{¼%ounce} leaves from stems. Discard stems. Finely chop leaves. Thinly slice @button mushrooms{4%ounce}.

Toss mushrooms with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, rosemary, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} on a #baking sheet{}. Roast in oven until browned and lightly crisped, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, cut @brie{4%ounce} cheese into thin slices. Spread @fig jam{1%ounce} on one side of two of the @whole wheat bread{4%slice} slices. Top jammy sides with brie slices. Place remaining slices of bread on top of each to create two sandwiches.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium-low heat. Add sandwiches and cook until nicely browned on outside and melty inside, ~{4-5%minutes} per side.

While sandwiches cook, toss mushrooms with @arugula{4%ounce}, a large drizzle of @balsamic vinegar{2%tablespoon}, and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a large #bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper.

Slice sandwiches in half and serve with salad.

> This version of grilled cheese is spiffed up with brie and sweet fig jam, perfect for dinner or any time you want to keep things classy.